.TH RIECOIN-WALLET "1" "May 2025" "riecoin-wallet 2505" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
riecoin-wallet \- manual page for riecoin-wallet 2505
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B riecoin-wallet
[\fI\,options\/\fR] \fI\,<command>\/\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Riecoin Core riecoin\-wallet utility version 2505
.PP
riecoin\-wallet is an offline tool for creating and interacting with Riecoin Core wallet files.
.PP
By default riecoin\-wallet will act on wallets in the default mainnet wallet directory in the datadir.
.PP
To change the target wallet, use the \fB\-datadir\fR, \fB\-wallet\fR and (test)chain selection arguments.
.SH OPTIONS
.HP
\fB\-datadir=\fR<dir>
.IP
Specify data directory
.HP
\fB\-dumpfile=\fR<file name>
.IP
When used with 'dump', writes out the records to this file. When used
with 'createfromdump', loads the records into a new wallet.
.HP
\fB\-help\fR
.IP
Print this help message and exit (also \fB\-h\fR or \-?)
.HP
\fB\-version\fR
.IP
Print version and exit
.HP
\fB\-wallet=\fR<wallet\-name>
.IP
Specify wallet name
.PP
Debugging/Testing options:
.HP
\fB\-debug=\fR<category>
.IP
Output debugging information (default: 0).
.HP
\fB\-printtoconsole\fR
.IP
Send trace/debug info to console (default: 1 when no \fB\-debug\fR is true, 0
otherwise).
.PP
Chain selection options:
.HP
\fB\-chain=\fR<chain>
.IP
Use the chain <chain> (default: main). Allowed values: main, test,
regtest
.HP
\fB\-testnet\fR
.IP
Use the test chain. Equivalent to \fB\-chain\fR=\fI\,test\/\fR.
.PP
Commands:
.IP
create
.IP
Create a new descriptor wallet file
.IP
createfromdump
.IP
Create new wallet file from dumped records
.IP
dump
.IP
Print out all of the wallet key\-value records
.IP
info
.IP
Get wallet info
